## üìè FILE SIZE & MODULARIZATION RULES (CRITICAL)

### Hard Limits (STRICT)

- **Max 250 lines per file** (hard limit - no exceptions)
- **Max 50 lines per function** (extract to helper functions)
- **Max 3 levels of nesting** (refactor if deeper)
- **If file exceeds limits ‚Üí automatically split into modules**

### When to Split Files

#### Component Files (>200 lines)

**Extract to:**

- `[ComponentName].hooks.ts` - Custom hooks
- `[ComponentName].types.ts` - TypeScript types/interfaces
- `[ComponentName].utils.ts` - Helper functions
- `[ComponentName].styles.ts` - Style-related code (if needed)
- `[ComponentName]/components/` - Sub-components directory

**Example:**

```typescript
